e="text-align: right;">850.000</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;">5</td>\r\n<td>Deluxe Sea View - tripble<br />(Bedroom: 1,2 +1,6m. Area: 20-22m<sup>2</sup>)</td>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;">8</td>\r\n<td style="text-align: right;"></td>\r\n<td style="text-align: right;">900.000</td>\r\n<td style="text-align: right;">1.000.000</td>\r\n<td style="text-align: right;">1.000.000</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h4>Note: SALE OF 30% From 06 Sep 2011 to 31 Dec 2011 and to 01 Jan 2012 to 14 May 2012</h4>\r\n<h4>Room Facilities</h4>\r\n<ul class="checklist">\r\n<li>International telephone service</li>\r\n<li>Airport Transfer</li>\r\n<li>Tour/Travel Information Service</li>\r\n<li>Laundry Service</li>\r\n<li>Free Internet</li>\r\n<li>Cars, motorbikes Rental</li>\r\n<li>Room Service</li>\r\n<li>Restaurant service</li>\r\n<li>Support 24/7</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Include:</strong></p>\r\n<ul class="checklist">\r\n<li>Breakfast</li>\r\n<li>5% sevice fee</li>\r\n<li>Free Internet</li>\r\n<li>Excluding VAT and other services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\r\n<ul class="checklist">\r\n<li>Free for children under 12 years old</li>\r\n<li>Extra bed: 150.000 VND</li>\r\n<li>Check-out time: 12h00</li>\r\n<li>Check-in time: 14h00</li>\r\n<li>Payment: American Express, Diners Club, JCB, MasterCard, Visa</li>\r\n<li>Guests in groups, long term stay will be special prices</li>\r\n<li>Late check-out: to 18:00: The half-day, after 18:00: The one day</li>\r\n<li>50% deposit</li>\r\n<li>Cancellations are not refundable deposit.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p> </p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2009-08-11 04:38:40'),
(176, 'Location', '', 'location', '', '<div id="googlemap"><a href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=72&amp;Itemid=89"><img alt="Bản đồ vị trí Pearl Sea Hotel trên Google Map" height="500" width="680" src="images/stories/newmappsh.jpg" /></a>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2009-08-14 08:40:19'),
(177, 'Tickets for Da Nang International Fireworks Competition 2011 sold in Da Nang, Ha Noi and HCMC ', '', 'tickets-for-da-nang-international-fireworks-competition-2011-sold-in-da-nang-ha-noi-and-hcmc-', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Ngày 30-3, Sở VH-TT&amp;DL đã cập nhật và đưa vào danh sách 21 hoạt động phụ trợ của Cuộc thi bắn pháo hoa quốc tế Đà Nẵng 2011 (DIFC 2011). Đã thành thông lệ, đây chính là “phần nền” của sự kiện chính. Báo Công an TP Đà Nẵng điểm qua các sự kiện đáng chú ý trong số 21 chương trình này.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Hoạt động cộng đồng</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Trưng bày hiện vật cổ. Bộ sưu tập của lương y Lâm Vũ Xênh sẽ được giới thiệu tại Bảo tàng Điêu khắc Chăm, từ ngày 22-4 đến tháng 10-2011. Lâm Vũ Xênh nổi tiếng với bộ sưu tập hơn 300 cổ vật thuộc nền văn hóa Sa Huỳnh.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Liên hoan ẩm thực 3 miền và các món nướng, dự kiến tổ chức từ ngày 27-4 đến 2-5. Tại đây sẽ giới thiệu các món ăn đặc trưng 3 miền Bắc, Trung, Nam, bên cạnh đó sẽ trình làng nhiều món hải sản nướng. Các món ăn nổi tiếng của Italia như mỳ sợi, bánh pizza cũng được đưa vào thực đơn. Hỗ trợ cho chương trình này là các hoạt động biểu diễn, chơi thể thao trên biển, ca múa nhạc dân tộc và hoạt động của các ban nhạc Philippines. Liên hoan diễn ra ở không gian rộng của Ocean Club, bãi biển công viên Phạm Văn Đồng.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img height="300" width="450" src="images/stories/h4b.jpg" alt="h4b" /> <br />Khách quốc tế tham quan triển lãm mỹ thuật Việt Nam đương đại, sự kiện phụ trợ của DIFC 2010. Ảnh: V.T</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Triển lãm mỹ thuật toàn quốc do Cục Mỹ thuật - Nhiếp ảnh và Triển lãm, Bộ VH-TT&amp;DL tổ chức, từ ngày 27-4 đến 17-5. Tại đây, các tác phẩm điêu khắc, hội họa, nhiếp ảnh, nghệ thuật trình diễn của các nghệ sĩ cả nước được giới thiệu tại Bảo tàng Đà Nẵng.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Ca nhạc, thời trang “Sôi động phố biển” dự kiến diễn ra tại Công viên Biển Đông, tối 27-4. Với các nội dung như nhảy Aerobic kết hợp Hip-hop, trình diễn bartender (pha chế rượu), biểu diễn các ca khúc về phố biển và thời trang dạo phố, thời trang biển..., chương trình hứa hẹn sức hút lớn đối với người dân và du khách.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Đại nhạc hội “Lung linh sắc Việt” do Tập đoàn Mặt Trời – Cty CP Cáp treo Bà Nà và Cty N.T.H đăng cai tổ chức tại Cung Thể thao Tiên Sơn ngày 1-5 dự kiến sẽ là một cuộc hội tụ của nhiều ngôi sao ca nhạc, thời trang và sắc đẹp. Theo Ban tổ chức, các ca sĩ Hồng Nhung, Mỹ Linh, Hồ Ngọc Hà, Ngọc Anh, Quang Dũng, Tuấn Hưng, Kasim Hoàng Vũ, Hà Anh Tuấn, Uyên Linh, các danh hài Chí Tài, Hoài Linh, các hoa hậu Nguyễn Thị Huyền, Mai Phương Thúy, Nguyễn Thùy Dung cùng hàng loạt siêu mẫu nổi tiếng sẽ tham dự chương trình này.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Triển lãm giới thiệu sách “Mảnh đất và con người Quảng Nam – Đà Nẵng” diễn ra tại Thư viện tổng hợp Đà Nẵng (46 – Bạch Đằng) từ ngày 28-4 đến 3-5 sẽ giới thiệu 52 đầu sách đặc sắc về chủ đề trên.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img height="350" width="450" src="images/stories/h4a.jpg" alt="h4a" /> <br />Tái hiện phiên chợ quê. Ảnh: NET</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Điểm đến</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mỗi dịp thi bắn pháo hoa là mỗi lần Đà Nẵng giới thiệu về mình với hàng vạn du khách trong nước và quốc tế. Trong dịp này, hoạt động du lịch trở nên cực kỳ sôi động, với sự tham gia rộng khắp.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Chương trình Farmtrip đến tham dự và quảng bá cho du lịch TP sẽ đón các đoàn Nga, Nhật Bản và Trung Quốc. Sự kiện này có sự tham gia của Vietnam Airlines, Vitours, Cty Du lịch Đà Nẵng và các khách sạn lớn, như Silver Shores International Resort, Furama Resort.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Tour khám phá thiên nhiên do BQL Bán đảo Sơn Trà và một số đơn vị khai thác dịch vụ chủ trì sẽ giới thiệu đến du khách hàng loạt điểm đến kỳ thú, dịch vụ hấp dẫn, như lặn biển ngắm san hô, câu cá cùng ngư dân, khám phá Sơn Trà bằng ô-tô và tour “lên rừng xuống biển”.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Bên cạnh đó, hàng loạt chương trình tham quan khác do Cty Du lịch Đà Nẵng tổ chức cũng hứa hẹn sức hút lớn, như “Khám phá Bà Nà bồng lai tiên cảnh”, chương trình city tour khám phá phố biển hay các tour kết nối 2 di sản thế giới Huế - Hội An...</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Một hoạt động không thể thiếu trong dịp này là thả hoa đăng và diễu hành thuyền hoa trên sông Hàn, do Q. Sơn Trà chủ trì. Chương trình diễn ra mỗi tối, từ ngày 28 đến 30-4.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Bên cạnh các hoạt động giải trí, thưởng lãm, trong dịp DIFC 2011, rất nhiều hoạt động thể thao diễn ra từ ngày 15-4 đến đầu tháng 5-2011. Giải Bi sắt TP lần thứ II diễn ra tại Trung tâm VHTT Q. Ngũ Hành Sơn; Giải Futsan TP và Giải cầu lông truyền thống các CLB TP diễn tại Cung Thể thao Tiên Sơn; Giải vô địch cầu lông đồng đội nam nữ phối hợp toàn quốc diễn ra tại Trung tâm Thể thao Quân khu V...</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Hoạt động sớm nhất của DIFC 2011 đã diễn ra, đó chính là triển lãm đá Non Nước trên đường Bạch Đằng, bắt đầu từ tháng 1 năm nay.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Một tháng sôi động của TP Đà Nẵng đã bắt đầu.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">(<em>Nguyễn Lê - www.cadn.com.vn</em>)</p>', '', 0, 2, 1, '2011-04-06 03:14:59'),
(178, 'Google Map', '', 'google-map', '', '<div id="googlemap">{googleMaps lat=16.07363018702891 long=108.24258327484131 label="<strong>Pearl Sea Hotel Danang</strong><br />Add: My Khe Beach, Lot B2-09-10, Loseby St., Son Tra District, Danang city<br />Tel: (+84 511) 3925999 - 3917555<br />Mobile: (+84) 01215799799 - 0935 556649<br />Fax: (+84 511) 33917555<br />Website: www.pearlseahotel.com" width=690 height=690 zoom=16}\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2009-08-14 08:40:19'),
(179, 'Hoian Fullmoon Night', '', 'hoian-fullmoon-night', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Hoian fullmoon night This falls on lunar 14 every month - the day of the full moon. At night, Hoi An looks like a great stage, fanciful and briliant with colorful lanterns. Hoi An people wearing ancient clothes become actors in reciting poems, playing mah-jong and chess together. These activities relive the beautiful atmosphere of an ancient port with rural pleasures in traditional festivals. From 6.00 p.m till midnight, the whole ancient town are quite, and no vehicles. Both travellers and regional people, Vietnamese and foreigners go for a walk together in the cosy atmosphere with unforgetable memories.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Series of pictures of Hoian Fullmoon Night</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><img src="images/stories/lung-linh-dem-pho-co-hoi-an-1.jpg" width="550" height="366" alt="lung-linh-dem-pho-co-hoi-an-1" /></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><img src="images/stories/lung-linh-dem-pho-co-hoi-an-2.jpg" width="550" height="367" alt="lung-linh-dem-pho-co-hoi-an-2" /></strong></p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2009-09-09 04:14:49'),
(180, 'My Son Sanctuary', '', 'my-son-sanctuary', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">My son belongs to Duy Phu commune, Duy Xuyen district, Quang Nam province. My son temple area is located around 2 km2.in a small valley. My Son Sanctuary is a large complex of religious relics that comprises more than 70 architectural works. They include temples and towers that connect to each other with complicated red brick designs. The main component of the Cham architectural design is the tower, built to reflect the pinity of the king. For many centuries, the Cham built Lip, a mutually linked architectural complex, with baked bricks and sandstone.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img src="images/stories/my-son.jpg" width="800" height="462" alt="my-son" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The main temple worships the Linga-Yoni, who represents the capability of invention. Beside the main tower (Kalan) are several sub-towers worshipping Genies or deceased kings. Although time and the wars have destroyed some towers, the remaining sculptural and architectural remnants still reflect the style and history of the art of the Cham people. Their masterpieces mark a glorious time for the architecture and culture of the Cham, as `well as of Southeast Asia.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Each historical period has its own identity, so that each temple worshipping a genie or a king of a different dynasty has its own architectural style full of different impression. All of the Cham towers were built on a quadrate foundations and each comprises three parts: a solid tower base, representing the world of human beings, the mysterious and sacred tower body, representing the world of spirits, and the tower top built in the shape of a man offering flowers and fruits or of trees, birds, animals, etc., representing things that are close to the spirits and human beings. My son has been recognized as a world cultural heritage site on December 1999 by UNESCO.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Weather: There are 2 kinds of climate in Quang Nam: tropical costal climate and temperate highland climate. The annual average temperature is 25 oC. From February to April it is hot and dry. From September to November is rainy season. Annual average rainfall is 2000mm.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">How to get there: My Son is 70km Southwest of Da Nang city, 40km from Hoi An city. There is a daily bus from Da Nang to My son.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Railway: From Hanoi, Express train stop at Tam Ky station or Da Nang station and then take a bus to My Son (buses are available).</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2009-11-30 08:55:49'),
(181, 'Lễ hội Quán Thế Âm', '', 'le-hoi-quan-the-am', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><img style="float: left; margin-right: 5px; margin-bottom: 5px;" alt="Lễ hội Quán Thế Âm" height="210" width="320" src="images/stories/le-hoi-quan-the-am.jpg" />Lễ hội Quán Thế Âm được tổ chức hàng năm tại khu du lịch Ngũ Hành Sơn, thành phố Đà Nẵng. Lần đầu tiên được tổ chức vào năm 1960, nhân ngày khánh thành tượng Bồ Tát Quán Thế Âm ở động Hoa Nghiêm thuộc ngọn Thuỷ Sơn, phía Tây Ngũ Hành Sơn. Hai năm sau, lễ hội được tổ chức nhân dịp khánh thành chùa Quan Âm ở động Quan Âm, là nơi phát hiện một khối thạch nhũ có hình tượng Phật bà Quán Thế Âm. Sau đó, vì nhiều lý do, lễ hội không được tổ chức trong một thời gian khá dài. Mãi đến ngày vía đức Phật bà Quan Thế Âm vào năm 1991 (19/2 năm Tân Mùi), Lễ hội Quán Thế Âm mới được khôi phục trở lại. Từ đó, hàng năm, cứ đến ngày 19.2 Âm lịch, lễ hội lại được tổ chức với một tầm vóc, quy mô ngày càng lớn và nội dung ngày càng phong phú hơn. Lễ hội Quán Thế Âm diễn ra trong 3 ngày, bao gồm hai phần: lễ và hội.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<h4>Phần lễ: Mang màu sắc lễ nghi Phật Giáo với các nội dung:</h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">- Lễ rước ánh sáng: Nghi lễ rước ánh sáng thường tổ chức vào tối ngày 18, gồm rước đuốc, rước kiệu, múa lân, múa rồng để cầu mong ánh sáng soi đường cho chúng sinh, mà trong phật giáo ánh sáng đồng nghĩa với trí tuệ, trí tuệ sáng thì tấm lòng, đạo đức trong sáng, sẽ làm nhiều việc thiện.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">- Lễ khai kinh: Lễ được tổ chức vào sáng sớm ngày 19, đây là lễ cầu nguyện cho quốc thái dân an, chúng sinh an lạc.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">- Lễ trai đàn chẩn tế: lễ này cũng được tổ chức vào sáng ngày 19 để cầu siêu, cúng thập loại chúng sinh, thường trước đó đồng bào phật tử gởi danh sách những người thân của mình đã mất đến chùa để làm lễ cầu siêu. Trong lễ này phải mời người có giới phẩm đứng ra làm lễ.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">- Lễ thuyết giảng về Bồ tát Quán Thế Âm và dân tộc: lễ cúng được tổ chức vào sáng ngày 19, ngợi ca lòng từ bi bác ái của đức Phật Bồ Tát Quán Thế Âm và cầu nguyện cho dân tộc an bình, thịnh vượng.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">- Lễ rước tượng Quán Thế Âm: Lễ này tổ chức vào khoảng 10 giờ sáng ngày 19, sau các nghi lễ trên, bốn người khiêng kiệu trên có tượng Phật bà đi trước, và đồng bào Phật tử đi sau, kiệu được khiêng từ trên chùa và đi xuống chiếc thuyền đậu trên Sông Cầu Biện (nhánh của sông Cổ Cò), sau đó cho thuyền chạy vòng quanh sông Cổ Cò. Lễ này nhằm cầu nguyện cho đồng bào, chúng sinh đi biển, đi làm ăn trên sông nước được thuận lợi bình an. Ngoài các nghi lễ trên, còn có lễ tế xuân (cúng sơn thủy, thổ thần) để cầu quốc thái dân an. Lễ thường được tổ chức vào đêm ngày 18. Trong ngày lễ này các bô lão của các phường Hòa Hải, Hòa Quý khăn áo chỉnh tề, tay cầm cờ lọng, đuốc, lồng đèn, có đội nhạc cổ và chiêng trống đi theo. Sau khi làm lễ và đọc văn tế, đoàn bô lão sẽ dẫn đầu đoàn rước cộ xuống bờ sông Cầu Biện để mở hội hoa đăng, rồi từ chùa Quán Thế Âm đi quanh các khu phố qua các làng đá mỹ nghệ Non Nước, xuống khu du lịch Non Nước và trở về lại lễ đài với lộ trình dài hơn 2km.</p>\r\n<h4>Phần hội</h4>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Diễn ra sôi nổi với nhiều hoạt động văn hoá - thể thao mang đậm bản sắc dân tộc xen lẫn với hiện đại như hội hoá trang, hát dân ca, thi cờ, nhạc, hoạ, điêu khắc, múa tứ linh, thả đèn trên sông, hát tuồng... các hoạt động văn hóa như triển lãm thư pháp và tranh thủy mặc, hội thi thuyết minh về danh thắng Ngũ Hành Sơn, hội thi nấu ăn chay...</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Nhờ vào vị thế sơn thủy hữu tình, các nội dung phong phú của lễ hội đã thu hút khá đông khách hành hương cùng khách du lịch trong và ngoài nước đến với phía Tây thắng tích Ngũ Hành Sơn. Trên sân bãi, diễn ra trò chơi kéo co truyền thống. Ngoài phía sông Cổ Cò, vang tiếng hò reo của khách tham gia hội đua thuyền, hội đua thúng lắc. Khi đêm xuống, lễ hội càng lộng lẫy, hoành tráng với nhiều thanh âm và màu sắc. Sau khi ''Truyền thuyết Ngũ Hành Sơn'' được diễn xong ở sân khấu chính, các đội hình rước đuốc, rước cộ bắt đầu được diễu hành qua các đường phố chính của Ngũ Hành Sơn. Dưới sông, các cư sĩ chùa Quán Thế Âm thả hoa đăng, gửi lời cầu nguyện cho ánh sáng trí tuệ được trường tồn như dòng nước. Với nhiều hoạt động văn hóa - thể thao mang đậm tính dân tộc, lễ hội Quán Thế Âm tuy mang màu sắc tôn giáo nhưng lại đi sâu vào tự tình dân tộc, góp phần phục hồi và phát huy bản sắc văn hoá của dân tộc Việt Nam.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Lễ hội Quán Thế Âm là một lời cầu nguyện cho quốc thái dân an, cho mưa hòa gió thuận; là dịp để mọi người, mọi giới chan hòa trong không khí hội hè, soi mình vào bản sắc văn hóa dân tộc để ngày một sống đẹp hơn.</p>\r\n<p> </p>', '', 0, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 03:19:07'),
(182, 'Da Nang International Firework Competitor 2011 Acknowledgment', '', 'da-nang-international-firework-competitor-2011-acknowledgment', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The Danang’s People Committee has announced the competitors of the International Firework Competition. These include the host- Vietnam (Danang) and England (Jubilee Fireworks), Korea (Hanwha), Italy (Parente Fireworks A&amp;C SNC) and China (Panda Fireworks).<br />These delegates will participate in the Da Nang International Fireworks Competition in 2011. With its theme of “The Shimmering Han River” over two consecutive nights the 29th and 30th of April, 2011, the poetic Han River will showcase dramatic and the colorful firework performances of these 4 famous international firework champions as well as Vietnam. The Da Nang Police Newspaper will introduce interesting information about these champions in the year 2011.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img height="529" width="800" src="images/stories/phao-hoa-2011.jpg" alt="phao-hoa-2011" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In 2009, the romantic and classic love story of Luong Son Ba – Chuc Anh Dai performed by Liuyang Dacing (China) impressed viewers with music and the colorful lights of fireworks. The emotional moment have remained in the memories of those audiences since the harmonious night of 28/3/2009.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Now, the participation of Panda Fireworks Company marks the return of on “ancient friend” China in year 2011. Established in 1989, Panda is one of the most famous fireworks companies of China. It was certified as a Grade A fireworks performance, and was involved in composing Chinese Security Laws and Firecracker and Fireworks Security Laws in co-operation with the Security Ministry of China.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Furthermore, Panda is acknowledged as the leading fireworks company of the Chinese fireworks industry with many outstanding fireworks performances to its credit. Also, Panda Fireworks Company is well-known for its significant capacity to create fireworks performing art. Tourists present in Da Nang on the 29th and 30th of April 2011 will enjoy a very special performance on the program thanks to the outstanding record of Panda Fireworks: Participating in the International Exhibit Opening Ceremony in Shanghai 2010; The 10-year Establishing of Macao Special Zone Ceremony; The 60-year China Independence Day Ceremony; Performing in The Opening and Closing Olympic at National Bird Net Stadium, Being Acknowledged as the most beautiful fireworks music performance in Italy in 2006; The biggest performance at Firework Fair Hangzhou 2006, etc...</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Jubilee Fireworks Co. is a real champion in the fireworks industry in England. Established in 1987, Jubilee is a professional fireworks display company based in western West Midlands. Jubilee makes over 200 professional performances every year and often coordinates with other European companies on the occasion of major events.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Chris Pearce chief executive, and also company founder is a leader in the fireworks manufacturing industry and fireworks display in England. He was Chairman of the British Firework Frtisans Association (BPA) from 2002 to 2007 – the leading fireworks trade and industry agency in the England. For many years, Jubilee has represented England and attended many international competitions some of which include Macau, San Sebastian (Spain), Rome (Italy), Portugal, Philippines and Malta.<br /><br />Some recent awards include: the English Fireworks Championship in 2003 and the English Fireworks with Music Championship in 1999, the first prize in the Monaco International Fireworks Competition 2010, the first prize in the Philippines International Fireworks with Music in 2010 and the first prize in the English champions Competition in 2006, 2008.</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 03:24:42'),
(183, 'Ba Na, Chua Mountain, Mo Stream', '', 'ba-na-chua-mountain-mo-stream', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Located in Hoa Vang province, apart from Danang 40 kilometers to southwest, Ba Na – Mount Chua is 1,487 meters high over the sea level. Average temperature is from 17 to 20 degree Celsius.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In Ba Na, there are four seasons in a day: spring in the morning, summer at noon, autumn in the afternoon, winter in the evening. For light rains, it is not as wet as in Da Lat. Although it rains around the mountain, the top is dry; furthermore, it is cloudless, and fresh. Compared with Tam Dao, Da Lat, the territory has a precedence of panoramic view. From the top of the mountain, one can have a vast view of sea, Danang city, rice fields spreading to the horizon.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img alt="Bà Nà cáp treo đường lên tiên cảnh" height="343" width="800" src="images/stories/pano-bana-hills.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">While months from May to August are the hottest period (up to 32oC) in seaside Central Viet Nam, temperature at the territory fluctuates from 17 to 20 degree Celsius, 22-25oC in maximum. It drops down to 15oC at night. With temperate climate, murmuring rivers, fluttering trees, Ba Na is as attractive as Tam Dao, Da Lat, etc. The Ba Na natural reservation zone has 544 sorts of high-level flora, 256 types of animals, in which there are 6 flora and 44 fauna of being precious recorded in Vietnamese Redbook.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">One seems to be lost in clouds and smoke. For different factors and reasons, people have different judgments on Ba Na but all think that it is Ba Na that is the best place for relaxing.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">With its wonderful advantages, French chose the territory as a relaxing resort and constructed hundreds of castles, villas, pleasure house and buildings here. Though natural calamities and enemy inflicted destruction for half of century sweep some traces of these ancient houses and buildings, there remains generosity of nature: primitive forests, temperate and fresh climate, fluttering sounds of pine hills mixed with songs murmured by rivers flowing over granites and then smoothly towards the forest.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Some villas currently restored and upgraded with modern equipments are available. Especially comfortable telepheric system drives tourists from Vong Nguyet post, soaking in clouds, bypassing the beneath primitive forest to the center of Ba Na tourist site. Ba Na – a romantic site thanks to the beauty of nature embellished by human hands. Looking down to Danang from the top of Ba Na, one seems to have the feelings that one is living in a different life with different emotions and different happiness. Feelings one can never gain from life in noisy urban areas.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In connection with Ba Na – Mount Chua, Mo River is a famous tourist site. In direction of southwest about 27 kilometers from Danang, in Hoa Vang district, the site is most occupied in summer. There is Toc Tien Fall (Fairy’s Hair Fall) with 9 levels. The fall is called Toc Tien because looking up from the fall foot, it looks like a fairy’s beautiful hair.</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 04:01:35');
INSERT INTO `news` (`id`, `title`, `hash_tag`, `alias`, `image_url`, `introtext`, `fulltext`, `state`, `language_id`, `enabled`, `created_date`) VALUES
(184, 'Son Tra Peninsula', '', 'son-tra-peninsula', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Son Tra Peninsula is a low mountainous area fully covered by forest . It is one of the city’s  lung. Son Tra Peninsula and the Hai Van Pass embrace the Han River and form a wide closed bay. From the air, the Son Tra Peninsula looks like a fish fairy swimming to the Eastern Sea. From the sea, you can see three mountain peaks: Co Ngua, Nghe and Mo Dieu. The highest peak is 693m above the sea level.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img src="images/stories/pano-ban-dao-son-tra.jpg" width="682" height="250" alt="Bán đảo Sơn Trà" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">For tens of thousands of years, the peninsula was an island. However, alluvial soil deposited by rivers connected it with the mainland. From the peninsula, tourists can see the coast lines and enjoy  Danang Bay, Danang City, the Han river, the Hai Van Pass and the Marble Mountains. In the early nineteenth century, the Nguyen Dynasty built many defensive fortresses and observation posts here. In 1858, the French fired the first shot on the peninsula and started their invasion of Vietnam.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Nowadays, the peninsula’s tourism potentials have been aroused. Some entertainment areas have been built along the beaches. Tourists can go paragliding and ride in motor boats. You can also go to fish farms, go around the peninsula by boat, go fishing offshore or go diving to enjoy the colourful coral reefs.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Son Tra Natural Preservation Zone</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The 4,439 ha zone includes 4,180 ha of forest with 3,431 ha of forest area (2,806 ha of natural forest and 625 ha of afforested area), and 748 ha of uncultivated area.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The zone consists of a wet ecological coastal  system and a primeval tropical forest. It has diverse tropical flora and rare species at risk of extinction.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The zone has many beautiful landscapes and historical relics. It is also the source of the fresh water supply for the city  and is considered a barrier protecting the city from winds and storms.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Visiting Son Tra Peninsula</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">- Location: Tho Quang Ward, Son Tra District. A road around the peninsula along the city’s beaches and on to Hoi An Old Town has been built. Many tourist zones have been put into use or are being built. Visitors can stay here and bathe at the beautiful beaches.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Tourism services include bathing, mountain climbing, scuba diving,  fishing and visiting caged fish farms. Tourists will also be instructed how to catch cuttle-fish and shrimp, go water-skiing and paragliding and eat “goi ca” (fresh fish mixed with lemon and vegetables) on board.</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 06:08:47'),
(185, 'My Khe Beach', '', 'my-khe-beach', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">With 900 meters long, My Khe beach is the most crowded of Danang beaches and popular to local people.American soldiers occupied a part of the beach before 1975. They established some premises for their relaxation and recreations. And now it has some enabling conditions such as being near the city’s center, large space, beautiful landscapes, and qualified services (hotels, restaurants, vehicles keeping site, fresh water bathing, sunshade and buoy lease, etc.). There are 50 well-equipped and comfortable bedrooms and lots of services in My Khe hotel. Many luxurious seaside villas with over 100 rooms are available for families, working staff. They can come here to play and rest at weekend.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img alt="Bãi biển Mỹ Khê" height="393" width="800" src="images/stories/pano-my-khe-new.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Coastal specialties like shrimps, crabs, fish, cuttles, etc. in hundreds of small shops with are at reasonable price. Life - saving groups are at work all days to guarantee safety to visitors.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Han River suspension bridge was completed, it links the east to the west area, making transportation possible. Consequently, My Khe beach becomes an attractive resort.</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 06:17:55'),
(186, 'Danang city', '', 'danang-city', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Situated in central Vietnam, Danang is Vietnam’s fourth largest city and a bustling sea port, located midway between Hanoi and Saigon. While Danang is an important economic hub for Vietnam, for tourists, it is primarily a transit point on to the nearby destinations of Hue and Hoi An or the beaches just outside the city.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img height="525" width="1076" src="images/stories/pano-song-han.jpg" alt="Khám phá Đà Nẵng bên bờ sông Hàn" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Danang is favored by nature, situated in the middle of the three world cultural heritage sites including the ancient capital Hue, the ancient town Hoi An and the holy land My Son. Such the position highlights the Danang''s role in Central Vietnam. This is the place for welcoming, serving and being the entrepot for tourists. Not only at the central point of the three world cultural heritages, Danang City has also lots of attractive spots which tourists feel unforgettable after visiting the city.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Danang has the high and dangerous Hai Van pass with full of perilous obstacles, engraved “the most grandiose beauty spots in the world”, Son Tra peninsula - an ideal rendez-vous for tourists. Surrounding Son Tra peninsula are Da stream, Bai But, Bai Rang, Bai Bac, Bai Nom - the beautiful alluvial plains which make interesting feeling for tourists on being ingulfed in splendid of dawn and the quietness of crepuscle in a picturesque land. The eco-tourism resort Ba Na - Mo Stream is considered as Dalat, Sapa of Central Vietnam and the legendary Marble Mountains - "a beautiful landscape of the southern heaven and earth".</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mentioning Danang, tourists can not forget the poetic Han river and its bridge - the first swing one in Vietnam. This is the pride of Danang people. The Han River bridge - the symbol for new vitality and the developing desire of the city- was built with the contribution of all the city''s people. It seems that all poetic features of the Han River can be only expressed deeply in the space of Han River bridge with full of wind and ventilation. It not only facilitates transport and potentials for tourism, awaking economic potentials of a vast area in the eastern city but is a cultural spot of Danang people today left behind for the future generations.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Danang is also endowed with sea - the vast tourist source of inspiration. In addition to beautuiful and clean stretching beaches, Danang seaport is one of the most well-known seaport in Vietnam.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Danang City by Han river - a poetic and beautiful sea city plus the hospitability of the city people make it a frequent destination for domestic and international tourists.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>What to Do?</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">While Danang is frequently bypassed by tourists, it has several tourist attractions to justify a stop, most notably the world-renowned Cham Museum in Danang.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">A trip to the My Khe Beach, or one of the other beaches, is also a popular activity from Danang for relaxing, swimming and watersports. The beaches in this area also have some of the best waves for surfing in the country.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Nearby My Khe Beach is the Marble Mountain, five marble mountain each representing a natural element and caves to explore. Further from Danang is the Ba Na Hill Station, 42 km west of Danang, with spectacular vista views, waterfalls, light trekking, and cool temperatures.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>When to Go ?</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The weather in Danang stays relatively warm and mild year-round. There are two seasons in Danang, with the rainy season from August to December and the dry season from January to July. Protected by the Hai Van Pass from the northern winds and rains, the weather is milder and dryer than destinations just to its north. The city’s average temperature is about 26ºC, rising to 28-30ºC from June to August and cooling to 18-23ºC from December to February.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>How To Get There ?</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Air:</strong> Danang Airport is located just 3 km southwest of the city center, with frequent flights to Hanoi and Hochiminh City on both Vietnam and Pacific Airlines and daily flights to Nha Trang, as well as international services direct to Bangkok, Hong Kong, Siem Riep, Taipei and Singapore.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Train:</strong> Danang is a major station of the Reunification Train system, with trains running several times per day both north towards Hue and Hanoi and south towards Nha Trang and HCMC. The Danang train station is located about 1.5 km north of the city centre.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Bus:</strong> Danang is well-served both by public buses at Danang’s intercity bus station to Hue (108 km, or three hours), Hoi An (30 km, or less than 1 hour), Hanoi (764 km, or 16 hours) and HCMC (964 km, or 24 hours). Danang is less served by the open-tour buses, which generally pass briefly through Danang on the way to Hoi An and Hue.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Car:</strong> With Hoi An less than an hour away (and costing only $10-15 USD), many tourists prefer to go by taxi or private car from Danang to Hoi An. Private cars can also be arranged for Hue, Ba Na Hill Station, My Son, Bach Ma National Park.</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 06:24:04'),
(187, 'Indochina food court', '', 'indochina-food-court', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Judging from the formal, luxurious and quiet appearance of this building from the outside,  it is hard to imagine that there is actually a busy food court inside, on the third floor. Of course the price here is a little higher than normal restaurants (ranging from 30,000 to 70,000VND for a dish), but it is a fun place to spend time with friends and family. This food court overlooks the beautiful Han river and Han bridge with fantastic view from the window.</p>\r\n<img alt="Indochina food court" src="images/stories/food-court.jpg" />\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">So this is how it works: in front of the food court there is a counter where you can buy electronic cards. Depending on how much you''re gonna eat, you can buy the 50,000 100,000 or 200,000VND cards. Then you can use that prepaid card to buy food from several counters inside. In the end, if you don''t use up that card, you can go back to the counter and have the remaining money back.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">How to order: Once you''ve ordered, give the card to the staffs at the food counters and they will slide it on a machine. They will then give you a plastic sign with a number. Then you can take that sign with you and sit wherever you want, they will bring the food to your table once it''s ready.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">There are around 10 counters with a wide range of food. 2 of them have Korean and Italian food. The food here is very nice and clean.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">So if you want a change from eating at small street vendors, or want a nice and polite place to go with colleagues, friends, families, lovers, this is it.</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 06:47:19'),
(188, 'Danang Seafood', '', 'danang-seafood', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Let the pictures say it all. Enjoy!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img alt="oc_bien" src="images/stories/oc_bien.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img alt="muc_mot_nang" src="images/stories/muc_mot_nang.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Where: seafood restaurants along the beach or on Son Tra Peninsula.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">There is also one famous restaurant called Ms. Thoi - 96-98 Le Dinh Duong. Its only downfall is lack of beach atmosphere as it is located in the city centre.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">When: afternoon or evening</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Price: varies from shop to shop. Averagely, around 300,000VND for 1kg of crabs, 60-70,000VND for 1kg of clams.</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 06:54:03'),
(189, 'Banh xeo', '', 'banh-xeo', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Bánh xèo (literally "sizzling cake") are Vietnamese savoury pancakes made out of rice flour, water, turmeric powder, stuffed with slivers of fatty pork, shrimp, and bean sprouts and then pan fried. Traditionally, they are served wrapped in mustard leaf, lettuce leaves, and stuffed with mint leaves, basil, fish leaf and/or other herbs, and dipped in a prepared nước mắm called nuoc cham (Vietnamese fish sauce thinned with water and lemon). In the Central region, the pancake is dipped in a special ''tuong'' sauce which consists of liver, hoisin sauce and garlic. (Wikipedia)</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img alt="banh_xeo" src="images/stories/banh_xeo.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This is by far my most favourite dish of Danang. So much that if I must recommend only one dish to introduce Danang food, I would unhesitatingly choose this over many other great dishes. Why? Because it is absolutely delicious and "edible" to anyone. The sauce doesn''t include any special "nuoc mam" (fish sauce) so don''t worry if you can''t stand nuoc mam''s smell. In fact, the sauce is the key element which separates good and not so good Banh xeo, and makes Banh xeo in Danang unique and different from those in other cities. Most shops also sell "nem lui" together with banh xeo, so don''t forget to try them as well.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The best and most famous shop for Banh xeo in Danang is without doubt "Ba Duong" (literally means "Mrs Duong". If you''ve noticed, lots of food shops in Central Vietnam begin their names with "Ba". Well, lucky lucky Central misters). This shop is located in a very small street but is always crowded. There are around 4 more banh xeo shops opened up in that incredibly narrow street just to compete with "Ba Duong", so make sure you get to the right shop. If you ride a motorbike, make sure you park in Ba Duong''s parking lot if you don''t want to receive unfriendly glances from other shop owners. Well this may sound troublesome, but believe me, the hot sizzling delicious pancakes worth a try ;)</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 07:01:57'),
(190, 'Lẩu and the drinking culture', '', 'lau-and-the-drinking-culture', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Hot pot is a(nother) distinctive feature of Vietnamese cuisine. There are, again, many kinds of hot pot, and the most popular main ingredients are fish, beef, and seafood. Aside from the main ingredient, there can be tomato, tamarind, and different kinds of vegetables, depending on what and where you eat.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In Da Nang (and some other cities as well), the best hot pots are usually sold in "quán nhậu" which is a type of Vietnamese drinking establishment. These "quán nhậu" serve a wide range of side dishes that may be hard to come across elsewhere, and I must say these dishes are great. It can get very noisy at these places with men drinking and talking; it can be fun or annoying depending on your mood. People, mainly men, go to these places after working to drink with their friends for fun, or with guests for business. Japan, (and I think some other Asian countries), also shares a similar culture.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img alt="lau" src="images/stories/lau.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Anyway, back to the main subject. My most favourite hot pot is the one with eel-fish at this place called "Liêm" on Le Hong Phong street. Their hot pot''s broth is just great. I''ve tried hot pots at other places as well but nothing came close (just to my taste and preference; you may feel different). Their other dishes are also amazing. I especially LOVE the sweet and sour beef tendon, and the fried chicken wings (deep-fried with fish sauce).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Hot pot is just a perfect choice for chilly rainy days, so make sure to try one before the next hot sunny season comes.</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 07:04:28'),
(191, 'Nem - Cha - Tre', '', 'nem-cha-tre-some-special-food-from-pork', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">To bring your relatives these delicious specialties after a lovely trip to Danang City, you should contact with the following places to tailor your own reservation.</p>\r\n<img src="images/stories/tre-ba-de.jpg" alt="Tré Bà Đệ" />\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span currenttext="* Some famous addresses: " ispart="true" class="xml-text">Some famous addresses</span>:</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span currenttext="Cha Huong " ispart="true" class="xml-text">Cha Huong </span><br historytouched="false" dirty="false" /></strong><span currenttext="Add: 04 - Hoang Dieu st - Tel: 0511.3828821 " ispart="true" class="xml-text">Add: 04 - Hoang Dieu st - Tel: 0511.3828821 </span><br historytouched="false" dirty="false" /><strong><span currenttext="Nem tre ba De " ispart="true" class="xml-text">Nem tre ba De </span><br historytouched="false" dirty="false" /></strong><span currenttext="Add: 81 - Hai Phong st - Tel: 0511.3828067 " ispart="true" class="xml-text">Add: 81 - Hai Phong st - Tel: 0511.3828067 </span><br historytouched="false" dirty="false" /><strong><span currenttext="Nem tre ba Cuc " ispart="true" class="xml-text">Nem tre ba Cuc </span><br historytouched="true" dirty="false" /></strong><span dirty="true" currenttext="Add: 107 Hai Phong st - Tel: 0511.3891770" ispart="true" class="xml-text">Add: 107 Hai Phong st - Tel: 0511.3891770</span><span dirty="false" currenttext="&lt;/" ispart="true" class="xml-punctuation"></span></p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 07:09:31'),
(192, 'Cam Le sesame candy', '', 'cam-le-sesame-candy', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">With main ingredients being rice powder, sugar, ginger, and especially sesame, this candy used to be so popular in local farmer families. Formerly, it was a common practice for families in the region to make it as their agricultural offering to their ancestors in festivals and ceremonies. Nowadays, the making of it became less popular but is still alive in the area near Cam Le River. Just 10 minutes by motorbike from the city center and you get to see how they make this candy.</p>\r\n<img alt="Khô mè Bà Liễu" src="images/stories/kho-me.jpg" />\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span class="xml-text" ispart="true" currenttext="* Some reliable addresses: ">Some reliable addresses: </span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span class="xml-text" ispart="true" currenttext="Mrs Lieu’s shop: ">Mrs Lieu’s shop: </span><br dirty="false" historytouched="false" /></strong><span class="xml-text" ispart="true" currenttext="Add: An Hoa, Khue Trung ward Tel : 0511.3846723 ">Add: An Hoa, Khue Trung ward Tel : 0511.3846723 </span><br dirty="false" historytouched="false" /><strong><span class="xml-text" ispart="true" currenttext="Mrs Lieu’s retail shop ">Mrs Lieu’s retail shop </span><br dirty="false" historytouched="false" /></strong><span class="xml-text" ispart="true" currenttext="Add: 50 Ngo Gia Tu st. Tel: 0511.3822297 ">Add: 50 Ngo Gia Tu st. Tel: 0511.3822297 </span><br dirty="false" historytouched="false" /><strong><span class="xml-text" ispart="true" currenttext="Mrs Nhut’s Shop ">Mrs Nhut’s Shop </span><br dirty="false" historytouched="false" /></strong><span class="xml-text" ispart="true" currenttext="Add: Cam Le, Khue Trung Ward Tel : 0511.3846754 " dirty="true">Add: Cam Le, Khue Trung Ward Tel : 0511.3846754 </span></p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 07:14:37'),
(193, 'Bun cha ca', '', 'bun-cha-ca', '', '<p>This is a famous morning dish in Danang. Its main ingredient is poached or grilled ground fish, and the broth is made from tomato, pineapple, pumpkin, bamboo shoot and other herbs.</p>\r\n<p><img alt="lau" height="376" width="500" src="images/stories/lau.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p>Bún chả cá is well-known and distinctive in Central Vietnam where fishery is one of the most vital professions  of the local people. The fish are thus always fresh and best in quality. Made from different kinds of fruits and herbs, Bún chả cá is tasty and nutritious at a low price. So what more can you ask for!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Where: </strong></p>\r\n<p>1. Bun cha ca - 61B Le Hong Phong - 13000VND</p>\r\n<p>2. Hờn - 113/3 Nguyen Chi Thanh - 13000VND</p>\r\n<p><strong> When:</strong> Usually in the morning but also available all day.</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 07:19:51'),
(194, 'Professionalizing the organization of the International Fireworks Competition 2011 in Danang', '', 'professionalizing-the-organization-of-the-international-fireworks-competition-2011-in-danang', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">On the afternoon of 29th Oct, the Standing Committee of Da Nang City held a meeting where functional departments reported plans for the Da Nang International Fireworks Competition in 2011.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The Da Nang International Fireworks Competition in 2011 with the theme of “The Shimmering Han River” over two nights the 29th and 30th of April, is expected to have five teams attending from England, Korea, Italy, China, and a host Vietnamese team (Danang).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><img height="281" width="500" src="images/stories/lung-linh-song-han.jpg" alt="Lung linh sông Hàn 2011" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Up to this time, the City People''s Committee and other Departments have promoted a fund mobilizing plan for the fireworks fund, increasing advertisement and widely introducing the competition through live broadcast on national and local television stations. Plans of building stages, bleachers for viewers, infrastructure and customs procedures as well as fire and explosion prevention are also being considered and evaluated.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Speaking at the meeting, Mr. Nguyen Ba Thanh, Party central committee member - Party Secretary, emphasized that preparation for the funding, infrastructure investment, and equipment purchases as well as organizing professional teams with specific styles, safety and impressiveness must be truly professional for the success of the Competition. He requested that the departments and related companies push the funding campaign early and decisively to raise 70-100 billion VND for the fireworks fund. He also emphasized the well – organized task of printing Firework tickets and ensuring absolute safety, order and security, traffic and fire prevention.</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-03-01 11:44:49'),
(195, 'Introduction Pearl Sea Hotel', '', 'introduction-pearl-sea-hotel', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Welcome to the Pearl Sea Hotel.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The Pearl Sea Hotel made it’s grand opening at the beginning of April 2011. It has a unique type of architecture and is considered a three star hotel. This ten story hotel has forty five rooms with all modern amenities making you feel comfortable like at home. The hotel staff are professional, friendly and caring and are ready to accommodate our guests.</p>\r\n<p><img width="690" height="190" alt="Biển Mỹ Khê " src="images/stories/new-pano-my-khe.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The Pearl Sea Hotel is in an ideal location. We are a walking distance from My Khe beach considered by many as one of the most beautiful beaches in the world. At this beach the American soldiers first landed in 1965 to begin the Viet Nam War. From the hotel you have an exquisite view of the pristine Son Tra peninsula, along with the panorama of Da Nang. Also seen from the Pearl Sea Hotel is both famous folding Song Han and Thuan Phuoc bridges. We are 7 minutes away both from Da Nang International Airport and Da Nang Center of Business and Commerce. .</p>\r\n<table border="0" style="width: 100%;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;"><a rel="gb_image[]" title="Pearl Sea Hotel" href="images/stories/HH1.jpg"> <img src="images/stories/SH1.jpg" alt="Pearl Sea Hotel" /></a></td>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;"><a rel="gb_image[]" title="Pearl Sea Hotel" href="images/stories/HH2.jpg"><img src="images/stories/SH2.jpg" alt="Pearl Sea Hotel" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h4>It’s a comfortable drive from our hotel to the most popular tourist places:</h4>\r\n<ul class="checklist">\r\n<li>Ba Na Hills – Cable  cars (35 km, 45 min.)</li>\r\n<li>Ancient  town of Hoi An – an old trading center of the Chinese, Japanese and Portugees , one of ten   popular tourist towns of the world (30 km, 45 min.)</li>\r\n<li>Cù lao Chàm Island - a beautiful island with various wild animals and legendary landscapes (12 miles, 25min.)</li>\r\n<li>Cham Island – Wild life preserve (12 nautical miles, 90 min.)</li>\r\n<li>Ancient  ruin of Cham towers (70 km, 90 min.)</li>\r\n<li>Mountain pass Hai Van  (40 km, 45 min.)</li>\r\n<li>Hue city - Former imperial capital of Viet Nam (110 km, 120 min.)</li>\r\n<li>Peninsula  Son Tra, Bodhisattva Linh Ung Tu’s  memorial  (5 km, 7 min.)</li>\r\n<li>Ngu Hanh Son mountain peaks, village of fine handicrafts of Non Nuoc ( 7 km, 10 min.)</li>\r\n<li>My Khe beach – one of the six most beautiful beaches of the world ( 300 m, 5 min.)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<table border="0" style="width: 100%;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;"><img src="images/stories/bana-hill.jpg" alt="Bana Hill" /></td>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;"><img src="images/stories/ngu-hanh-son.jpg" alt="Marble Mountains" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;">Bana Hill</td>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;">Marble Mountains</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;"><img src="images/stories/pho-co-hoi-an.jpg" alt="Hoian Ancient Town" /></td>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;"><img src="images/stories/thanh-dia-my-son.jpg" alt="My Son Sanctuary" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;">Hoian Ancient Town</td>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;">My Son Sanctuary</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2009-06-29 03:23:57'),
(196, 'Thông tin phòng nghỉ', '', 'thong-tin-phong-nghi', '', '<ul class="checklist">\r\n<li>Tầng dưới có các phòng thuận tiện cho người lớn tuổi thích đi bộ, trẻ nhỏ nô đùa chạy nhảy. Còn các phòng trên cao có tầm không gian ngắm biển, buổi đêm có thể mở cửa đón gió vào trong giấc ngủ say, buổi sáng thức dậy với ánh bình minh chào ngày mới.</li>\r\n<li>Với không gian thiết kế thoáng đãng, quý khách có thể sử dụng thang máy hoặc thoải mái theo cầu thang bộ theo những bảo tàng nho nhỏ lý thú dọc tường để lên ban công tầng trên cùng. Từ trên cao, quý khách có thể ngắm nhìn bán đảo Sơn Trà, Ngũ Hành Sơn ngay bên cạnh, đèo Hải Vân mây vờn với núi, cáp treo Bà Nà thấp thoáng chốn tiên cảnh, Cù lao Chàm xa xa và hít thở đại dương bao la trước mặt.</li>\r\n<li>Các phòng nghỉ được công nhận đạt chuẩn 2 sao, trang tiện nghi hiện đại, có đầy đủ máy điều hòa LG mới, thiết bị phòng vệ sinh Caesar, tắm nóng lạnh, tủ lạnh, tivi 21” truyền hình cáp, điện thoại, internet Wifi, cửa sổ Eurowindow, thang máy… với giá cả hợp lý.</li>\r\n<li>Dưới chân bạn là bãi tắm số 1 biển Mỹ Khê, 1 trong 6 kỳ quan biển do Forbes bình chọn.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a class="readon" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=70&amp;Itemid=53">Xem chi tiết...</a>', '', -2, 2, 1, '2009-08-11 04:38:40'),
(197, 'Tickets for Da Nang International Fireworks Competition 2011 sold in Da Nang, Ha Noi and HCMC', '', 'tickets-for-da-nang-international-fireworks-competition-2011-sold-in-da-nang-ha-noi-and-hcmc', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">For greatest convenience for spectators everywhere, tickets for the Danang International Fireworks Competition 2011 will be sold in Da Nang, Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh City.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">At the meeting that reviewed the preparations for the Danang International Fireworks Competition 2011 (DIFC 2011) on 15 Feb, Chairman of Da Nang Committee Tran Van Minh agreed to the policy which is 16,068 tickets at stage B (B1, B2, B3) will be sold at 200,000 VND a ticket for one person in one night for city residents and visitors. Ticket are on sale in Ho Chi Minh (1 venue), Hanoi (1 venue) and at 5 venues in Danang City such as Department of Culture, Sport and Tourism, the Nguyen Hien Dinh Classical Drama Theatre, the Trung Vuong Theatre, the Tourism Promotion Center and Viet Art Join-stock Company.</p>\n<img height="772" width="1167" src="images/stories/phaohoa1-4.jpg" alt="phaohoa1-4" />\n<p style="text-align: justify;">To meet the needs of those enjoying fireworks displays from boats, Chairman Tran Van Minh also agreed on guidelines which allow boating travel agencies to sell tickets, however, safety and quality of services must be committed. Fare sales must not exceed 200,000 VND a ticket for one person per night. The border guards headquarters is responsible for the organization of boating agencies’ ticket sales to visitors and the general list of authorized agencies is set by the Danang Department of Culture, Sport &amp; Tourism.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The Danang People''s Committee has also agreed to choose the stage construction plan DIFC 2011 submitted by the Joint-stock Indochina Corporation, including two stages: Stage A is the main stage with a capacity of over 9,000 seats and stage B is in a broad area of the Olalani projects with a capacity of around 16,000 seats.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The Danang International Fireworks Competition 2011 will be held by the Han River, Danang city on two nights, the 29th and 30th Apr 2011 with the subject "Sparkling Han River". Da Nang-Vietnam is the host team, and 4 other international teams from England, Korea, Italy and China will also compete. Global 2000 Companies continues to be selected as the consulting office by Danang People''s Committee in this competition.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In the framework of the fireworks festival, many extracurricular activities also take place such as sophisticatedly-decorated boat parades, flower garlands and coloured lanterns on the Han River, the Non Nuoc stone exhibitions, beautiful photo exhibitions about international fireworks competition this year, beach sports performances and organizations, music and fashion shows "Exciting coastal city." ...</p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-04-06 03:20:43'),
(198, '4 quốc gia tham dự cuộc thi bắn pháo hoa tại Đà Nẵng', '', '4-quoc-gia-tham-du-cuoc-thi-ban-phao-hoa-tai-da-nang', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Cuộc thi bắn pháo hoa quốc tế Đà Nẵng năm 2011 sẽ diễn ra bên bờ sông Hàn (Đà Nẵng) trong 2 đêm 29 và 30/4 với chủ đề "Lung linh sông Hàn". Ban tổ chức sẽ bán vé tại 3 điểm chính là Đà Nẵng, Hà Nội và TP HCM.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Theo Ban tổ chức, ngoài đội chủ nhà Đà Nẵng, cuộc thi sẽ có sự góp mặt của 4 đội tuyển đến từ Anh, Hàn Quốc, Italia và Trung Quốc. Công ty Global 2000 tiếp tục được UBND thành phố chọn làm đơn vị tư vấn.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Trong khuôn khổ lễ hội, nhiều hoạt động phụ trợ sẽ diễn ra, như: diễu hành thuyền hoa, hoa đăng trên sông Hàn, triển lãm tượng đá Non Nước, trình diễn hoạt động thể thao biển, chương trình ca nhạc và thời trang “Sôi động phố biển”...</p>\r\n<div style="text-align: center;"><img alt="Phao-hoa-02" height="290" width="450" src="images/stories/Phao-hoa-02.jpg" /></div>\r\n<div style="text-align: center;">Pháo hoa rực sáng trên sông Hàn.</div>\r\n<p>Để phục vụ cuộc thi, UBND thành phố Đà Nẵng đã đồng ý chọn phương án xây dựng khán đài của Công ty cổ phần Đông Dương, gồm khu khán đài A tại sân khấu chính với sức chứa hơn 9.000 chỗ và khu khán đài B tại khu đất trống dự án Olalani với sức chứa khoảng 16.000 chỗ. Giá vé tại khán đài B là 200.000 đồng một người.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Ngoài ra, UBND thành phố Đà Nẵng đã cho phép các đơn vị có tàu du lịch bán vé trên tàu xem bắn pháo hoa, tuy nhiên phải có cam kết đảm bảo về an toàn, chất lượng dịch vụ và giá vé không được quá 200.000 đồng một người một đêm.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Cuộc thi bắn pháo hoa quốc tế được thành phố Đà Nẵng tổ chức mỗi năm một lần. Tại cuộc thi lần thứ 3 năm 2010, ngoài chủ nhà Đà Nẵng, có 4 đội quốc tế tham gia là: Bồ Đào Nha, Mỹ, Nhật Bản và Pháp.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">(<em>Minh Nhật - www.vnexpress.net</em>)</p>', '', 0, 2, 1, '2011-04-08 03:10:47'),
(199, 'Bản đồ vị trí Pearl Sea Hotel trên Google Map', '', 'ban-do-vi-tri-pearl-sea-hotel-tren-google-map', '', '<div id="googlemap">{googleMaps lat=16.073403379873454 long=108.24449300765991 label="<strong>Pearl Sea Hotel Danang - Khách sạn Biển Ngọc</strong><br />Địa chỉ: Lô B2-09-10, đường Loseby, An Cư 3, Quận Sơn Trà, TP Đà Nẵng<br />Điện thoại: (+84 511) 3925999 - 3917555<br />Di động: (+84) 01215799799 - 0935 556649<br />Fax: (+84 511) 33917555<br />Website: www.pearlseahotel.com" width=690 height=500 zoom=15}\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>', '', -2, 2, 1, '2009-08-14 08:40:19'),
(200, 'Khuyễn mãi', '', 'khuyen-mai', '', '<img alt="Thông tin khuyễn mãi" height="90" width="680" src="images/stories/newkm.jpg" />', '', 0, 2, 1, '2011-04-07 03:45:24'),
(201, 'Han River: Sparkling in the firework festival night 2011', '', 'han-river-sparkling-in-the-firework-festival-night-2011', '', '<p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">With the permission of the Prime Minister, since 2008, Danang has been honored to be the host of International Firework Contest every year. This is the cultural and tourism event of international stature that Danang has organized successfully attracting the attention of a wide participation of residents and visitors, contributing to the brand development of modern Danang City - dynamic and innovative in the new era, and created a good opportunity to stimulate the city in developing strongly tourism, services and investment attraction in the country.</p>\r\n<p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><img height="326" width="480" src="images/stories/DN5.jpg" alt="DN5" /></p>\r\n<p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Since the past three years, the images of beautiful firework displays colorfully bursting in the melodious music stream on sparkling Han River night has been imprinted in the heart of Da Nang residents and visitors whenever referring to the beautiful city of peace by the river and by the sea. The world class performances shown by the teams from five continents bring to viewers the true strange and different feelings, create an international class playground, reunion and is becoming a brand, a unique tourism product  of the City.</p>\r\n<p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">To follow the success of the past 3 years, on 29th  and 30th April 2011, Da Nang city continue to organize the International Firework Contest with the participation of England (Jubilee Fireworks Company),  Korea (Hanwha Companyn), Italy (Parente Fireworks A &amp; C SNC Company), China (Panda Fireworks Company) and the host team -  Vietnam (Danang City). The international teams has been selected based on quality, capacity and ranking in the international firework competition in the world, this promises to give Danang International Fireworks Contest 2011 many gorgeous and attractive displays bringing the unique color of each team.</p>\r\n<p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">This year, Da Nang city will continue to build the stage system consisting of two zones:  stand A at the main stage with a capacity of over 9,000 seats for invited guests and stage B on an empty land of Olalani Project with the capacity of  about 16,000 seats to sell tickets for residents and visitors with the price of 200,000 VND per person per ticket per night. In order to create favorable conditions for residents and visitors, Da Nang City arranges ticket selling post in Ho Chi Minh (1 point), Hanoi (1 point) and 5 points in Danang consisting of Department of Culture, Sports and Tourism, Nguyen Hien Dinh Theatre, Trung Vuong Theatre, Center for Tourism Promotion and Viet Art Joint Stock Company. Besides, the city also allows companies owning tourism boats to sell tickets for enjoying firework on boat. However, they have to commit on the safety, service quality and the ticket price can not exceed 200,000 VND/person/night.  . Residents and visitors who have no conditions to buy tickets to the stages  or to boats can enjoy the fireworks display on the Bach Dang street, Tran Hung Dao Street, the Han River, Thuan Phuoc bridge ...</p>\r\n<p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">In the scope of contest, the city will also host many ancillary activities such as Displaying firework on computer, Music program before the contest performed by Trung Vuong Theatre, Art programs on the main stage by Lam Son Company (Hanoi). Many other supporting activities will be held such as the flower boat parade, displaying flower galands and coloured lantern on Han River, Non Nuoc Carved Stone Exhibition, the Third Beautiful Photoes of Firework Exhibition, Grilled Food Exchange Festival, Performance and organization of sports activities, music, fashion, Light  decoration Art at My Khe beach...</p>\r\n<p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">In recent years, each contest, each show has brought many different impressions. The participating teams have studied much about the culture and history of Vietnam and Da Nang to build the impressive performance. For example, the performance by the Portuguese team with the theme "Dragon and fire - the birth place of legendary" takes viewers back to a time when the legends about dragons and fairy appeared. The touching  love story of the fairy Au Co traveling down and trapped on the earth, tears of the fairy flowing into the Han River is displayed by the brilliant colorful light of firework by the French team. Similarly, the famous love story of Luong Son Ba - Chuc Anh Dai by Chinese team has brought real emotions in the audiences’ hearts. The characteristic sounds of the didgeridoo of the natives in Australia has brought audiences to the endless steppes of the kangaroo country, or the dazzling firework display filled with lively music of the U.S. team has demonstrated a unique culture of the country  ...</p>\r\n<p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">In the past three years, we could see the attraction of the contest as well as the warmly welcome atmosphere of the residents and international friends through the fact that all the hotels in the city were already booked, tickets for the Firework Contest Enjoying were fully reserved in the beginning of the year; the national airline of Vietnam increased  tens of flights to Da Nang during this time, but all the tickets were sold out ... On the nights of the performance, hundreds of thousand of residents and tourists filled the stages and all buildings and roads nearby. That is to say that Danang International Firework Contest has succeeded brilliantly bringing to Da Nang and  Vietnam a unique cultural and tourism event of international stature.</p>\r\n<p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">To conclude, I would like to quote the saying of Mr. Tran Van Minh - Chairman of Danang People’s Committee: “ With all the special favours from the Nature and the tireless efforts of man, flowers have bloomed on this gentle and beautiful city so that  Danang will always attract visitors near and far and become a beloved and missing  part to those who have ever come to Da Nang.</p>\r\n<p style="TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Series of pictures of DIFC 2010</p>\r\n<table cellpadding="3" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="text-align: center; width: 207px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><img height="296" width="450" src="http://www.dothi.net/News/Tin-tuc/Doi-song-do-thi/2010/03/3B9AEF18/Phao-hoa-01.jpg" border="1" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><img height="290" width="450" src="http://www.dothi.net/News/Tin-tuc/Doi-song-do-thi/2010/03/3B9AEF18/Phao-hoa-02.jpg" border="1" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><img height="470" width="450" src="http://www.dothi.net/News/Tin-tuc/Doi-song-do-thi/2010/03/3B9AEF18/Phao-hoa-03.jpg" border="1" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><img height="470" width="450" src="http://www.dothi.net/News/Tin-tuc/Doi-song-do-thi/2010/03/3B9AEF18/Phao-hoa-04.jpg" border="1" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><img height="468" width="450" src="http://www.dothi.net/News/Tin-tuc/Doi-song-do-thi/2010/03/3B9AEF18/Phao-hoa-05.jpg" border="1" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><img height="390" width="450" src="http://www.dothi.net/News/Tin-tuc/Doi-song-do-thi/2010/03/3B9AEF18/Phao-hoa-06.jpg" border="1" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><img height="320" width="450" src="http://www.dothi.net/News/Tin-tuc/Doi-song-do-thi/2010/03/3B9AEF18/Phao-hoa-07.jpg" border="1" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>(<em>Đoàn Loan - www.vnexpress.net</em>)</p>\r\n<p> </p>', '', 1, 2, 1, '2011-04-08 03:14:13');
